<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-22T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-22T14:00:00-05:00" n="811" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d811">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/1000</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Cuba</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GWE1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gonzales</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-22T15:00:00-04:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 22, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>From War Trade Board:</p>
                        <p>No. 90. Referring yours June 12, 11 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d811fn1">Not
                                printed.</note> We are allowing American coal to go to Cuba for the
                            benefit of Cuba, and we prefer to have Cuban Government restrict the
                            sailings of all vessels from Cuba to Mexico by declining to allow them
                            to have the coal which we have shipped for Cuba’s own use. Please
                            arrange along these lines if possible.</p>
                        <p>Show to <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MHH1">Morgan</persName>.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>